posts.message:
Nice Trick to add to your .gitconfig file

lg = git config --global alias.tree 'log --graph --full-history --all --color --date=short --pretty=format:"%Cred%x09%h %Creset%ad%Cblue%d %Creset %s %C(bold)(%an)%Creset"'

Then go to your terminal and run the following: 
$ git lg

posts.caption: Google I/O Extended 2014 Cairo + Shorouk
posts.description:
Register Now: http://goo.gl/jVHXxk

Google I/O Extended is a viewing party, taking place in many locations around the world, in which developers gather and watch the Google I/O event over live streaming.

Google I/O is a yearly event organized by Google, it takes place at San Francisco, in which there are very exciting sessions and workshops for developers. The most exciting part of it is the keynote of each day, in which Google introduces their latest inventions and technologies, and what they are planning to offer during the next year.

@[104896376246850:274:GDG Cairo] & @[219683741468393:274:GDG Shorouk] are joining forces to bring you Google I/O 2014 experience right here. This year the keynote is focusing on three key themes: Design, Develop & Distribute.

Don't miss it and register now: http://goo.gl/jVHXxk

Event agenda will be released shortly, stay tuned.

Google+ Event: http://goo.gl/SPGPWU
Hashtages: #io14extended #io14
